******
[1] Stavropol
Date: 2 Aug 2013
Source: Stav.aif.ru [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
http://www.stav.aif.ru/health/news/90585


Two people contracted anthrax in the Stavropol region. The Rosselhoznadzor [Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Supervision] is working to identify the source of infection.

According to the press service of Rosselkhoznadzor for the Stavropol region, 2 inhabitants of the village of Solnechnodolsk have been hospitalized with suspected anthrax.

The outbreak was reported on a private farm. According to preliminary data, the source of the human disease may be meat [carcass] from sick sheep. Rosselhoznadzor is investigating the source of the infection and applying the appropriate measures to prevent spread.

--
