[2] Stavropol
Date: 5 Aug 2013
Source: Caucasian Knot [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
http://www.kavkaz-uzel.ru/articles/228223/


"The outbreak of anthrax in Izobilnenskaya district of the Stavropol Territory is localized; there is no threat to the people," said the acting head of the district administration, Vladimir Kovreshkin, today [5 Aug 2013].

As reported by the "Caucasian Knot," on 2 Aug 2013, 2 people in the village of Solnechnodol'sk with suspected anthrax were hospitalized. On 5 Aug 2013, the diagnosis was confirmed.

The outbreak of the disease was detected in a private courtyard in the 3rd district, Solnechnodolsk, reported Vladimir Kovreshkin. According to him, 2 people are infected, a monastery monk and an employee. The affected residents are hospitalized in the infectious disease clinic of the CRH Izobilny district and regional infectious hospital in Stavropol.

"The situation is completely localized. There is no threat to people. And the Administration Head locally, within the township Solnechnodol'sk, has introduced a state of emergency," Vladimir Kovreshkin told the Caucasian Knot.

On the monastery grounds, the cattle were vaccinated; the affected area where the infected animals were located was disinfected, and contaminated materials were burnt.

On the roads leading to the village, disinfection barriers and fire-quarantine posts were set up. Traffic police officers and experts of the State Veterinary Service are on duty round the clock to prevent unauthorized movement of possibly infected cattle out of the quarantine area. All vehicles are subject to disinfection, said Vladimir Kovreshkin.

Solnechnodol'sk village is one of the largest settlements in the Izobilnenskaya area.

