[3] Bashkortostan
Date: 6 Aug 2013
Source: Rossiyskaya Gazeta [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
http://susanin.udm.ru/news/2013/08/06/407972


Eleven residents of the village of Bashkir Urals are hospitalized with suspected anthrax. For 4 of them, the diagnosis is confirmed, writes "Rossiyskaya Gazeta." The village has been quarantined, and access is monitored by the police.

Ilgiz Nizams, the chairman of the Committee on Civil Defense, Emergencies and Administration, Yanaulsky District, said that the source of infection was contaminated meat from a slaughtered animal. "Almost immediately, a 23-year-old woman presented herself to the dermatologist at the central hospital. With her were 3 more people with complaints of skin abscesses. Suspecting anthrax, these patients were sent to the infectious disease ward of the central hospital in Yanaulskogo district.

Currently, the village is under a 2-week quarantine. More than 80 residents who had contact with the infected meat are under constant medical supervision. Police have cordoned off the village with round-the-clock security and post-decontamination.

