[One might ask why only cattle were post-exposure vaccinated in Stavropol when the initial problem was with exposure to contaminated mutton in an unreported ovine outbreak. According to another report (http://www.regnum.ru/news/1691775.html), they had some 140 sheep and goats, of which 100 were neither registered nor vaccinated, presumably adult stock.

Outbreaks were reported in Stavropol in 2007 and 2010 but only in cattle. Bashkortostan is new in reporting, but logically, the livestock disease has been there for some time out of official sight.

My heartfelt thanks to Natalia Pshenichnaya for the translations and to Sabine for the original reports.

